(a) Write $$x^2 + 10x + 2$$ in the form $$(x + a)^2 + b$$ where $$a$$ and $$b$$ are integers. 

\vspace{7cm}

\hfill \makebox[6cm]{\dotfill}

\hfill (2)

\vspace{0.3cm}

(b) Hence, or otherwise, write down the coordinates of the turning point of the graph of $$y = x^2 + 10x + 2$$

\vspace{2cm}

\hfill \makebox[4cm]{\dotfill}

\hfill (1)

